      1          /**
      2           *  @file
      3           *
      4           *  @brief      This module manages the process to download the setting file section and displacement data from the ACU
      5           *
      6           *      Handling of unaligned section data
      7           *      When we have more then one section of setting file and if the previous section does not end with the correct FLASH_ALIGNMENT than the previous
      8           *      or if FLASH_ALGINMENT size is greater than maximum data transferred through Reveal, even if there is one section only.
      9           *
     10           *      The following sequence is used
     11           *
     12          @startuml{SFUpdater_Unaliged_Section_Data_Handling.png}
     13              title SFUpdater handling Unaligned data Sequence Diagram
     14          
     15              (*) --> "Set first Section of Setting file"
     16              --> "Get one block of data in the current Section of Setting file"
     17              if "Is the received block size less than FLASH_ALIGNMENT" then
     18                  -->[true]   if "Is Data ends at unaligned address" then
     19                                --> [true] "Write block and clear the Temporary Buffer"
     20                                --> "Prepare next block to get"
     21                              else
     22                                -->[false] "Append data to Temporary buffer"
     23                                --> "Prepare next block to get"
     24                              endif
     25              else
     26                    -->[false] "Write to Flash"
     27                    --> "Prepare next block to get"
     28              endif
     29              "Prepare next block to get" --> if "Is there more data to get from current section" then
     30                 -u> [TRUE] "Get one block of data in the current Section of Setting file"
     31               else
     32                   --> if "Is there another setting file section to get" then
     33                     -u-> [TRUE] "Set next Section of Setting file"
     34                     -u> "Get one block of data in the current Section of Setting file"
     35                   else
     36                    --> [Ending process] (*)
     37                  endif
     38              endif
     39          @enduml
     40          
     41           *
     42           *  @copyright  Copyright 2015-$Date: 2015/07/01 13:51:14EDT $. Whirlpool Corporation. All rights reserved - CONFIDENTIAL
     43           */
